# Documentation Rules

Documentation should explain:
- What PrairieLog does
- Why it exists
- Tech stack
- API flow
- Example log payload
- Maven commands
- Docker/Podman commands when present
- Deployment notes
- MVP limitations
- Future plans

Do not oversell features that are not implemented.
Do not claim persistent log storage.
Do not claim full user authentication unless it exists.
Do not imply webhook URLs or ingestion tokens are safe to expose publicly.
